<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">
The species areolaris and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ichneumonoidea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ichneumonoidea ocellaris" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellaris">ocellaris</taxonomicName>
have often been treated as comprising a separate genus, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Platophion" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platophion" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platophion</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld, I. D." journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Gazette" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="55 - 65" title="Notes on the British Ophionini (Hym., Ichneumonidae) including a provisional key to species" volume="24" year="1973">Gauld 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brock, J. P." journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="57 - 97" title="A systematic study of the genus Ophion in Britain (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="125" year="1982">Brock 1982</bibRefCitation>
) but are now generally treated as a species-group of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophion" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ophion</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarzfeld, M. D." journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="191 - 206" title="Molecular phylogeny of the diverse parasitoid wasp genus Ophion Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Ophioninae)" volume="41" year="2016">Schwarzfeld et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
